(16795,666,'focus_area_detail_content_0_images_2_image','11'),(16796,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_0_images_2_image','field_60f7b3fd0d64d'),(16797,666,'focus_area_detail_content_0_images','3'),(16798,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_0_images','field_60f7b3540d64c'),(16799,666,'focus_area_detail_content_1_content','<h2>We are interested in research that could affect a large number of people</h2>\r\nWe primarily support biomedical research but our interests are not limited to any particular field, disease, condition, or population. Instead, we seek to identify scientific research that has the potential for high impact and is under-supported by other funders. We are excited to support high-risk and unconventional science when the potential impact is sufficiently large.\r\n\r\nWe are broadly interested in research that may lead to improved understanding of topics related to human health. We are most interested in research that could affect a large number of people. We typically identify portfolio areas by looking for metrics related to the number of lives affected (often starting with the World Health Organization Global Burden of Disease). We begin with landscaping exercises to identify important research topics that could have the greatest impact in a given area.\r\n\r\nOnce we understand the research gaps in these fields, we assess which gaps are underfunded and seem most amenable to progress if funded. Often as part of this process, we will attend scientific conferences and interview scientists as advisors, peer reviewers, or potential grantees. For more information, see our Guide for Grant Seekers.\r\n\r\nSome aspects of the following topics are currently of particular interest: broad spectrum antiviral drugs, universal influenza vaccine, basic immunology, chronic pain, cardiovascular disease, Alzheimer’s disease, mechanisms of aging, epigenetics, novel scientific tools and methods, under-studied or unusual biological phenomena, and research on how biomedical research may be improved. Additionally, we are interested in research that supports the further development of plant-based meat replacements.'),(16800,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_1_content','field_60f7bf90c773e'),(16801,666,'focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_0_message','The Following Open Philanthropy staff oversee the Scientific Research program.'),(16802,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_0_message','field_60f7c20cc7745'),(16803,666,'focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_0_staff','a:3:{i:0;s:3:\"366\";i:1;s:3:\"364\";i:2;s:3:\"360\";}'),(16804,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_0_staff','field_60f7c09cc7743'),(16805,666,'focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_1_heading','Open calls for proposals'),(16806,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_1_heading','field_60f7c263c7748'),(16807,666,'focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_1_content','We are open to receiving unsolicited short pre-proposals at <a href=\"mailto:science@openphilanthropy.org\">science@openphilanthropy.org</a>. We try to consider all proposals but are unable to respond in most cases.'),(16808,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_1_aside_1_content','field_60f7c246c7747'),(16809,666,'focus_area_detail_content_1_aside','a:2:{i:0;s:10:\"staff_list\";i:1;s:13:\"short_message\";}'),(16810,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_1_aside','field_60f7bfdbc7740'),(16811,666,'focus_area_detail_content_2_heading','Scientific Research, at a glance'),(16812,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_2_heading','field_60f87b900096a'),(16813,666,'focus_area_detail_content_2_statistics_0_type','custom'),(16814,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_2_statistics_0_type','field_60f87c88d9f31'),(16815,666,'focus_area_detail_content_2_statistics_0_title','Portfolio<br> Areas'),(16816,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_2_statistics_0_title','field_60f87bb30096c'),(16817,666,'focus_area_detail_content_2_statistics_0_number','6'),(16818,666,'_focus_area_detail_content_2_statistics_0_number','field_60f87bcf0096d'),(16819,666,'focus_area_detail_content_2_stati